node.text: This is Wings of Rescue. Our sponsor, @titosvodka, will match up to $20,000 in donations sent their way through the link in our bio. Wings of Rescue flies dogs like Clyde from overcrowded shelters and disaster areas to shelters with empty kennel space where they’ll be adopted in no time. They’ve saved 8,597 pets this year already and can save way more with your help. Everyone involved gets a 14/10 from us [EDIT: initial goal of $20k hit in 45 minutes, secondary goal of $40k hit in 3 1/2 hours]

node.text: This is Lilac. She attempted a Houdini-like escape from her crate yesterday. She ended up hurting her front right leg. We’ve paid the remaining hospital bills for the surgery to fix it. Please consider getting pet medical insurance. It’s best to be puppared. 13/10

node.text: This is Boomer. At just 1.5 years old, he’s been diagnosed with fibrosarcoma in his jaw. Without surgery, he only has a few months left. Boomer was a gift from the family’s grandpa just before he passed. He’s the last little piece of him they have. You can help them save Boomer by clicking the link in our bio. 13/10 [EDIT: fully funded in 9 minutes, link in bio switched to Koda, who hurt her leg jumping for a toy and has surgery today!]

node.text:
This is Frida. She was found paralyzed in the middle of a busy street in Thailand. Her rescuers sponsored her medical care for several months before bringing her back to the states with them. With extensive physical therapy, a @justfoodfordogs diet, and a whole lot of love, Frida is doing wonderfully.

Paralyzed dogs like her often face frequent bladder infections, skin issues, and inflammation, but a fresh whole food diet of @justfoodfordogs has kept her happy and healthy. #partner

She inspires her humans every day, and it’s an honor to share her story with you. Bonus pic of her favorite socks (which conveniently match her favorite toy) at the end. 14/10 (follow @frida_strong)
